Key Findings

Opening Bar Dominance (HOD)

Bar 1 (09:00-09:15 CET) makes the high of day 21.2% of the time. The first hour collectively accounts for 32.4% of all session highs.

Opening Bar Dominance (LOD)

Bar 1 makes the low of day 22.4% of sessions — the strongest signal in the data. First-hour LODs comprise 37.8% of all session lows.

Critical Benchmark: By the 1-hour mark (10:00 CET), 68.6% of sessions have revealed at least one extreme. By the 2-hour mark (11:00 CET), this rises to 82.3%. The opening range is exceptionally predictive for intraday structure.

Trading Implications

Opening Range Definition

Over 1 in 5 sessions (21.8% average) establishes a critical extreme in the first 15 minutes. Mean reversion trades fading Bar 1 extremes face a ~21-22% base rate of that bar holding as the session boundary.

Time-of-Day Structure

Sessions reveal significant edge bias. Bars 1-8 (opening 2 hours) and the final bar (17:15-17:30) collectively account for the majority of extremes. Mid-session bars (10-25) show lower frequency, suggesting consolidation phases.

Directional Signals

When Bar 1 makes an extreme, subsequent price action has established the range boundary 21.2% (HOD) or 22.4% (LOD) of the time. This creates asymmetric risk/reward for directional continuation vs. reversion setups.
